result.execSummary:
The defendant Kevin Terrell Spencer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kevin Terrell Spencer in court with attorney Gregory Allan Renden.  Defendant Kevin Terrell Spencer in custody.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for sentencing. Court wanted to know why the defendant was previously revoked from electronic monitoring. Defense counsel advises the court that the defendant removed his bracelet on 1/11/2011.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

As to Count 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, with credit for 22 days time served. 
The court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on probation with the WI Department of Corrections for a period of 18 months. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Court orders defendant to serve 14 days in the House of Correction. 
-Serve 90 days in the House of Correction STAYED pending a review on 4/8/2016 at 1:15 pm in Branch 38.
-Attend and successfully complete Batterers Intervention OR Anger Management and continued programming.
-AODA and recommended treatment including random urine screens/Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
-Attend and successfully complete treatment and counseling programs as deemed appropriate by agent.
-NO CONTACT with the victim, UNLESS requested by victim and then only with prior approval of agent or the court.
-3rd party contact for the purpose of time with child(ren) as approved by agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY costs, assessments, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by Dept of Corrections by the end of probation.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means. ANY CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO BE APPLIED.
-Provide DNA sample, pay costs and DNA surcharge.
